## ðŸ§  3. **Index Marking** â€“ *"Mark the Floor Trick ðŸ”¨"*

### ðŸ“Œ When to use:

* When numbers are from 1 to n and **you donâ€™t want extra space**.

### ðŸ’¡ Idea:

Use the **array itself as a hash map**.
Mark `nums[i]`'s position as **negative** to say â€œthis number is presentâ€.

---

### âœ… Example: `Find All Disappeared Numbers` â€“ Optimized

```cpp
vector<int> findDisappearedNumbers(vector<int>& nums) {
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
        int index = abs(nums[i]) - 1;
        if (nums[index] > 0)
            nums[index] *= -1; // mark visited
    }
    
    vector<int> res;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
        if (nums[i] > 0)
            res.push_back(i + 1); // not visited = missing
    }
    return res;
}
```

